\par }\pard\plain \qj\fi284\sl240 \f2\lang2057 {\f6 
\par }{\f6 The configuration phase consists in the creation and construction of a page. The user can create}{\f6  and modify a page calling the tool named "}{\b\f6 config}{\f6 " both for synoptic and regulation scheme. A number of Editors are available.
\par }{\f6 
\par }\pard \qj {\b \{bmc config.bmp\}
\par }\pard \qj\fi284\sl240 {\b\f6 
\par }{\b\f6 Creation
\par }{\f6 
The user can create a new page selecting "Page" or "Regulation" on the Create pulldown menu. MMI will then display a window where basic information on the page geometry can be inserted. With the first choice MMI creates a synoptic and with the second a re
}{\f6 gulation page.
\par }{\f5 For regulation schemes management every page is associated with a progressive num}{\f5 ber, formed by numbers and characters, i.e.:
\par }{\f5 00,01, ... , 0A, 0B, ... , 0Z,10,11, ... , ZZ
\par }{\f5 These numbers are not re-computed after deleting a page.
\par }{\b\f6 
\par }{\b\f6 Construction
\par }{\f6 First, the user must instantiate one or more objects retrieved from a library and then select a graphic object to assign the resources using the attributes configurator named Resource Editor.
\par }{\f6 Furthermore the user can complete the page with the background by using the Draw Editor. 
\par }{\f5 In construction of regulation schemes once instantiation has }{\f5 been completed the user has to connect the objects's ports. Snap is available to facility the building of connections}{\f6  .
\par }{\f6 
