\par }\pard\plain \qj\fi284 \f2\lang2057 {\f6 
\par }{\f6 The Resource Editor allows to view and to edit the resources of every object both in the page and in the library.
\par }\pard \qj {\b \{bmc mi_remw.bmp\}
\par }
\par Not editable resources are also displayed but specified buttons and text fields are insensitive, as some resources are editable in libraries but not on page.
\par \pard \qj\fi284 {\f6 The Resource Editor is called by the user once the object has been }{\strike\f6\ul selected}{\v\f6\ul !}{\v\f6 PopupId(`gloshelp.hlp',`}{\v\f6\ul lgc_gl_gph_select}{\v\f6 ')}{\f6 
 by choosing Resource on Edit's pulldown menu or Resource on the pop-up menu (which is recalled from the third mouse button pressed on page/library). 
\par }{\f6 LEGOMMI displays a window containing the page name and class of the parent, a pulldown menu, the name of the object being edited, an option m}{\f6 
enu to choose the resource class, the list of the selected resources and the "Apply" and "Load" (Resources) buttons.
\par }{\f6 Available resource classes are:
\par }{\f6 Geometric
\par }{\f6 Specific
\par }{\f6 Color attributes
\par }{\f6 Change color var. 1
\par }{\f6 Change color var. 2
\par }{\f6 Change color var. 3
\par }{\f6 Change color var. 4
\par }{\f6 
\par }{\f6 "Geometric" are standard resources that define all the geometrical characteristics of the object (X, Y, Width, High, Rotate, Transparent) and some colors.
\par }{\f6 "Specific" are typical of every kind of object and contain resources like the ob}{\f6 ject type (i.e. pointer, bar for an indicator etc.).
\par }{\f6 "Color attributes" define the object's typical colors.
\par }{\f6 The other four ones, if available for the object, allow to associate an object portion with different colors depending on the values taken on by the variable chosen.
\par }{\f6 
\par }{\f6 Every group is set by selecting an option on the option menu and displayed inside a scrolled window. The above figure displays the "Specific" resources group of the icon.
\par }{\f6 Every row contains a resource but there are different display}{\f6 ing modalities. 
\par }{\f6 The button and text field are available when an Editor is necessary (Color, Font, Bitmap) to insert the modification. The button, featuring a label with the resources name, activates the editor while the text fields display the resource.
\par }{\f6 The label features the name and the text field when the user can directly insert the resource value.
\par }{\f6 The label features the name and the option menu to ascribe the resource value (i.e. a type or a rotation).
\par }{\f6 
\par }{\f6 Once a resource has been modified to the ri}{\f6 ght of the text field a little line is displayed.
\par }\pard \qj {\b \{bmc mi_remod.bmp\}
\par }\pard \qj\fi284 {\f6 
\par }{\f6 
Through the "Apply" push button the Resource Editor sets the current resource directly on the object. Through "Load" (Resources) push button the resources of the currently-selected object are loaded on the same window. The same operation is available also
}{\f6  through the File's pulldown menu with "Load Resources". The other options, -"Reset resources" and "Close"-, restore the condition prior to the editing of the individual resources and }{\f6 close the page.
\par }\pard\plain \s254\ri-6\keepn\tx-568\tx10773 \shading1000 \b\f2\fs36\expnd12\lang2057 {\plain \b\f6\fs36\up6\lang2057 \page }{\f6 #{\footnote \pard\plain \s29\qj\fi284\tx-568 \f2\lang2057 {\b # lmi_con_var_ed}}}{\f6 K{\footnote \pard\plain 
