\par }\pard\plain \qj\fi284 \f2\lang2057 {\f6 
\par }{\f6 Through the Variable Editor the user can select a variable from the set data base (simulator label on the config main window). The Editor reaches the variable by selecting first the module and the module block and then the block variable. 
\par }{\f6 Variable Editor main window:
\par }\pard \qj {\b \{bmc mi_ved1.bmp\}
\par }\pard \qj\fi284 {\f6 
\par }{\f6 The three selections above can be made by pressing the "List" push buttons. Once the List push buttons have been clicked, selection windows will be displayed. The}{\f6 
y contain respectively the list of models, the list of blocks of the selected model and the variable of the selected block.
\par }{\f6 
First the user must choose the Model and  the block then, by clicking the second "List" push button. The window which will be displayed features two lists containing the modules (and also the "All" choice) and the blocks respectively. If the user selects 
}{\f6 a particular module and then clicks "Filter" the block list will be updated only with the blocks of that module; if "All" has been s}{\f6 elected, all the model blocks will be displayed.
\par }{\f5 In the regulation model construction regulation scheme is like a module and coincides with a model block.
\par }{\f6 After the model and the block have been selected the user can choose the variable.
\par }{\f5 
\par }{\f6 In order to easily configure a desired variable a number of filters are available.
\par }{\f6 The filters "Component" and "Sub System" can be activate through an option menu and "All" will deselect filters. These filters, if activated, reduce the number of elements displayed ins}{\f6 
ide model and block lists, according to the Component or Sub System chosen.
\par }{\f6 
\par }{\f6 Variable Editor allows to load configuration information on a variable related to an object of the drawing area which has already been selected by pressing the "Grab Selected Widget" push button.
\par }{\f6 
\par }{\f6 When the editor is called during the configuration of an interactive object such as a button it is possible to assign a perturbation. Available perturbations are Not, Step, Pulse, Ramp, UpDown.
\par }{\f6 
\par }\pard \qj\fi284\sl240 {\f6 A view of Variable Editor windows is }{\f6 available in:
